author: Leslie Sattler
title: Conservationists spearhead massive 'nature haven' with community input: 'The sky's the limit'
text:
Plans are underway to transform up to 2,471 acres of farmland into London's largest nature haven.
This groundbreaking project, known as the Enfield Chase Landscape Restoration Project , is set to expand on the amazing woodland restoration work already happening at Enfield Chase in north London, according to BBC .
Over the past four years, an impressive 140,000 trees have been planted in the area. And now, the project is taking things to the next level by launching a public consultation in June to get residents' input on how to make this "nature haven" even more incredible.
According to John Cole, chairman of Friends of Enfield Chase, the possibilities are endless.
"The sky's the limit," he told BBC. "There's an opportunity for the likes of ramblers, runners, and cyclists to know more about it and put it on the map."
He envisions opportunities for outdoor enthusiasts to explore and enjoy the space. Sculpture parks, allotments, tree nurseries, and community gardens are just a few of the ideas that could become a reality if there's enough interest.
Watch now: Expert explains key contributor to recent wave of intense hurricanes But it's not just about creating a beautiful space for people to enjoy. This project has the potential to make a real difference for the environment and the local community. By restoring rivers , reducing flooding, and improving habitats for wildlife, the Enfield Chase Landscape Restoration Project is taking important steps toward a more sustainable future.
And the best part? The project is all about involving the local community. Enfield Council and the charity Thames 21 are working hard to ensure that all of Enfield's residents have a chance to get involved and have their say.
So, if you're a nature lover in London, now's your chance to use your voice and be a part of something special. Whether you want to get your hands dirty planting trees or simply enjoy the beautiful green space, the Enfield Chase Landscape Restoration Project has something for everyone.

title: What does 12/31/23 mean? The last day of 2023 is an angel number
text:
The coming year will be full of blessings, at least that's what the numerical sequence of this New Year's Eve date suggests.
If you take a closer look at the date written as 12/31/23 or even 123123, you may see an angel number, which are repeating number sequences that are often associated with deep spiritual exploration. Used as a guide for. The numerical sequences can range anywhere from 000 to 999, with each number having a different meaning and energy, as USA TODAY previously reported.
The once-in-a-century date, which won't be seen again on our calendars until December 31, 2123, marks a new beginning. One that, according to the Old Farmer's Almanac website, tells us to “change and evolve with the times and be in the right place to embrace what's coming to us.”
The date has also sparked an online trend, with TikTok users making videos on the number's significance and selling items celebrating the date online, including on platforms like Amazon, eBay and Etsy, according to the Detroit Free Press. Part of the USA TODAY Network. ,

What does 12/31/23 mean in numerology?
Numerology is an ancient esoteric science that deals with numbers and letters and the energies, intentions and vibrations behind them, professional numerologist Novalee Wilder shared with USA TODAY earlier this month.
“Even before there was language, there were numbers,” he said. “Before things were named, we counted them, and we gave meaning to that counting.”
The numbers that make up the angel number are just as important as the whole number, especially when you are trying to determine the vibration and intention behind the number.
Professional astrologer Narayan Montúfar tells Farmer's Almanac that “The number 1 brings the spark of initiation, 2 focuses on creation, and 3 relates to the concept of creation. Together, the sequence of these three numbers speaks of the spark of initiation. Who wants to create a new creation.
If you add together all the numbers that make up the date 123123, you will get 12.
The website states that the number 12 in numerology can symbolize spiritual enlightenment, with the day having the potential to deliver epiphanies and “aha” moments for individuals and society at large.

author: كتبت - مرام محمد
title: طلاب الثانوية العامة فى الجيزة عن امتحان الفيزياء: الأسئلة الاختيارية صعبة وتحتاج وقت - اليوم السابع
text:
أدى طلاب وطالبات الثانوية العامة بمحافظة الجيزة، اليوم الخميس، امتحان الدور الأول فى مادة الفيزياء لشعبتى العلوم والرياضيات، ومادة التاريخ للشعبة الأدبية، وذلك رابع أيام امتحانات العام الدراسي 2024-2025.
وشكا بعض طلاب الشعبة العلمية في مدرسة الأورمان الثانوية للبنات التابعة لإدارة الدقي التعليمية من صعوبة بعض أسئلة الاختيار من متعدد في امتحان مادة الفيزياء، مؤكدين أن أسئلة كثيرة في الامتحان كانت صعبة وفي مستوى الطالب فوق المتوسط وتحتاج إلى مزيد من الوقت للتفكير والحل.
وانطلقت لجان امتحان المادتين في تمام الساعة التاسعة صباحًا واستمرت لمدة ثلاث ساعات، وذلك وفقًا لجدول الامتحانات المُعلن من قبل وزارة التربية والتعليم.
وأوضحت وزارة التربية والتعليم والتعليم الفني، أن امتحان مادة الفيزياء للثانوية العامة 2025 اعتمد على أسئلة اختيار من متعدد ومقالية، مشيرة إلى أنه تم تخصيص 70% من الأسئلة للمستويات المعرفية البسيطة والمتوسطة و30% للمستويات المعرفية العليا.
ولفتت إلى أن امتحان الفيزياء، ضم 46 سؤالًا، تشمل 2 سؤال مقالي و44 اختيار من متعدد، بإجمالي 60 درجة، 56 درجة للاختيار من متعدد و4 درجات للأسئلة المقالية، وذلك لطلاب النظامين القديم والجديد بالثانوية العامة.
وأوضحت أن امتحان مادة التاريخ تضمن 46 سؤالًا، تشمل 2 سؤال مقالي و44 اختيار من متعدد، وذلك بإجمالي 60 درجة، 56 درجة لأسئلة الاختيار من متعدد، و4 درجات للأسئلة المقالية.

author: El Deber
title: Declaran alerta naranja, en 7 departamentos por tormentas eléctricas
text:
Declaran alerta naranja, en 7 departamentos, por tormentas eléctricas
La alerta naranja indica que existe un nivel de amenaza importante que contempla “fenómenos no habituales y con cierto grado de peligro para las actividades usuales del ser humano”, según la unidad de Pronósticos Meteorológicos.
El Servicio Nacional de Meteorología e Hidrología (Senamhi) pronosticó cielos nubosos con lluvias y tormentas eléctricas, a tiempo de lanzar una alerta Naranja, para los próximos días en lo sdepartamentos de: Tarija, Beni, Potosí, Cochabamba, Santa Cruz, Chuquisaca y La Paz, en el inicio de la gestión 2025.
“Se pronostican lluvias y tormentas eléctricas moderadas, temporalmente fuertes a ocurrir desde el viernes 3 hasta el domingo 6 de enero de 2025, en 7 departamentos; las principales regiones afectadas serán el eje central, con montos acumulados, de entre 30 a 90 milímetros (mm), de agua por metro cuadrado”, señala el comunicado oficial del Senamhi.
La alerta naranja indica que existe un nivel de amenaza importante que contempla “fenómenos no habituales y con cierto grado de peligro para las actividades usuales del ser humano”, según la unidad de Pronósticos Meteorológicos.
En las ciudades de La Paz y El Alto está previsto un descenso de las temperaturas, durante el primer fin de semana de 2025, según el reporte oficial.
Recomendaciones
Desde la oficina nacional del Senamhi se instó a que la población pueda llevar consigo paraguas ante eventuales lluvias; del mismo modo, realizar la limpieza de las bocas de tormenta, tanto en hogares como la vía pública, además de no botar basura en los canales de agua.
